# Twitter Guardrails (canonical: TWITTER_LOOP.md)

Whenever drafting ANY tweet, recap, or social copy for this project:

1. **Verify every number first.** Run `node scripts/socialRecords.mjs` (records)
   and `node scripts/socialBoard.mjs` (live board with time buckets). Never
   quote a W-L record, unit total, or pick that didn't come from these this
   session. Use the pick's `selection` field verbatim.
2. **Sound human.** Voice = `MY_VOICE_PROFILE.md`. Rotate post architecture
   (story / one-liner / desk note / question-first / ✅-recap) — never the same
   structure back-to-back. Banned: "let's dive in", "game-changer", "delve",
   default "tail or fade? 🎯" closers, 3-emoji rows.
3. **Sell without selling.** Proof and challenges ("bookmark this, grade us")
   instead of pitches. Site link ONLY in a ~25-min self-reply, never tweet 1.
   No hashtags.
4. **Prioritize top-tier picks inside 60 min of start.** Picks >60 min out MUST
   carry a natural line-movement reminder: sharp money moves, the site is the
   live truth, picks lock 15 min before start.
5. **Close on a real question** (2026 algo weights replies ~27x likes) and
   recommend a post window + first-30-min reply babysitting.
6. **Research with Firecrawl** (`FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` env secret,
   `https://api.firecrawl.dev/v2/search|/scrape`) for current viral formats
   before big posts; fold findings into `TWITTER_GROWTH_PLAYBOOK.md` (dated).
7. **Log every posted tweet.** When the user says they posted (any phrasing +
   URL), immediately run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs log --url <url>
   --draft <ready_to_post file> --pick <hero|altN>` (or explicit
   --structure/--mechanic tags for custom copy). Before writing new drafts,
   run `node scripts/socialLedger.mjs refresh` + `report` and let the
   structure/mechanic leaderboards pick the winning shape. Tag every draft
   candidate with structure/mechanic/refTag so logging works.

Full system + phases: `TWITTER_LOOP.md`. Drafts only — never post for the user.
